The paper discusses the importance of people as an integral component of the overall IoT infrastructure, which suggests that it belongs to the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-category. Additionally, the paper focuses on human-machine applications and user behavior, which are relevant to the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the impact of IoT on cybersecurity, which is relevant to the Cybersecurity (cs.CYBER) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the development of efficient incentivization mechanisms, which suggests that it belongs to the Multiagent Systems (cs.MA) sub-category.
